:"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"87f60321-3a77-05d6-7a00-04f2a0f775e7","name":"Note: Normalize Email Payload"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Classify with AI\n\nLLM classification into: Action Needed, Reference, Ignore (+fallback). Output port order matches this list.\n\nPorts: ①→ Store as Action Needed · ②→ Store as Reference, Capture Failure Context · ③→ Store as Ignore · ④→ Alert Outlook — Other\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"39163785-687f-7e3e-c773-c2ccaf56e79d","name":"Note: Classify with AI"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Anthropic Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Classify with AI** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 Anthropic API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[561,1090],"id":"b743961c-ada0-83f2-a602-1bc14c19770f","name":"Note: Anthropic Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Store as Action Needed\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,40],"id":"411f597f-08e7-9530-e059-9745f68e208b","name":"Note: Store as Action Needed"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Store as Reference\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,490],"id":"923eb4bf-7607-ff91-5319-52a0ce390c00","name":"Note: Store as Reference"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Store as Ignore\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1533,940],"id":"bb93c2e8-c1e5-1b21-db6e-2aac30e6a560","name":"Note: Store as Ignore"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Alert Outlook — Other\n\nmicrosoftOutlook — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1857,1390],"id":"f6443fcd-6c08-6d2c-839c-1c9ca0274b0f","name":"Note: Alert Outlook — Other"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Reunite Branches\n\nRejoins 4 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2505,520],"id":"7bb7da17-3af8-2803-6c1e-29ea64dd66b0","name":"Note: Reunite Branches"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nnotion — `getAll` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3477,520],"id":"429b212e-453a-3683-46fa-5213c5e9d6c0","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3801,520],"id":"10721795-88c5-3150-6614-1e038e9247a0","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4125,520],"id":"02d86be2-022a-4d68-669e-3b2ad00258ad","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4449,520],"id":"82ac406b-1683-c550-0ba1-245a18d3b4ea","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Copy to Google Drive","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,520],"id":"a72814ac-98a2-3758-ed54-2fec0a9c2df5","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Copy to Google Drive\n\ngoogleDrive — `upload` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fingerprint for Idempotency · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,520],"id":"6c388847-fb0f-70a9-0f43-831f57fe5c1b","name":"Note: Archive Copy to Google Drive"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per email (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,520],"id":"b84dd281-89b3-d1e4-41fd-28b34d4a3d78","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5745,520],"id":"7e6ba1f5-46ac-a7e5-a494-75c44b153249","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6069,520],"id":"6d9827e7-c83a-138b-97c5-d2f160c7407a","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6393,520],"id":"1ebcbe55-604b-d970-beba-c0c2a4af5e67","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6717,520],"id":"4c6cc14f-b786-417a-c654-dd98e550f52c","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Sort Emails Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7041,520],"id":"90447b9e-76cf-8270-cfc7-d914bd49584b","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Emails Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Tag Pipeline Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7365,520],"id":"296a79b4-2868-fb44-8162-cd524c423968","name":"Note: Sort Emails Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\nShapes the item: writes `pipeline`, `version`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Stamp Processing Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7689,520],"id":"12a6c69b-14da-5116-4028-5a9efa9e841b","name":"Note: Tag Pipeline Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Processing Time\n\nStamps `processedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8013,520],"id":"e8bb4649-5be4-b722-7d29-e591acf2bc49","name":"Note: Stamp Processing Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty from","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8337,520],"id":"4474b8b4-18ae-ea12-231a-2d437c1f1597","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty from\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8661,520],"id":"1ae5c2c1-f05a-5302-5d2b-25564067d017","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty from"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 25 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8985,520],"id":"e9959d9d-44f1-91e4-d49d-43f3980608f3","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9309,520],"id":"19a7be02-6ec7-d41b-6a21-e66a05bfcc0d","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9633,520],"id":"c177d6dc-6e00-e3c3-f1cf-d6d22aaeae2a","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9957,520],"id":"47d9ca55-c89d-00a8-a483-9752ff4b39bc","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9309,1540],"id":"5f1f7ce4-8142-23fd-6bd3-d3479c053efa","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9633,1540],"id":"10694096-e15b-a834-19d8-cf01428805e1","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9957,1540],"id":"112660a7-0968-48d0-08a8-081cc622e745","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Summarize meeting notes with Google Drive and Outlook hands-free\n\n**Pattern:** AI Summarize & Route · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nSummarize meeting notes with Google Drive and Outlook hands-free. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual inbox triage is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Normalize Email Payload → Classify with AI → Store as Action Needed → Reunite Branches → Load Previous Snapshot → Compute Drift vs Snapshot → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ai summarize & route without manual effort\n- Anyone automating inbox triage in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Responds in seconds\n- Improves response time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Anthropic API key; Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; Notion integration token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"a6356401-fd3d-eb10-809f-5498d42659f2","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"13c66381-b4d5-4a0f-8715-cb14e0746398","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"2ea4c3f7-2838-21da-d1ed-594991331e70","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"46e9dacf-098c-8510-2520-b049af8a544b","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your inbox triage process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-500],"id":"9bdf0b13-2327-5c07-b30f-104e695999e4","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Normalize Email Payload","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Normalize Email Payload":{"main":[[{"node":"Classify with AI","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Anthropic Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Classify with AI","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Classify with AI":{"main":[[{"node":"Store as Action Needed","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Store as Reference","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Store as Ignore","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Alert Outlook — Other","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Store as Action Needed":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Store as Reference":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Store as Ignore":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Alert Outlook — Other":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":3}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Reunite Branches":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Copy to Google Drive","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Copy to Google Drive":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Emails Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Emails Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Tag Pipeline Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Tag Pipeline Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Processing Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Processing Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty from","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty from":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"19810dc6-6154-4b95-bb43-6612c448899e","id":"FDX02364"}